  "event_preview": "World Wide Technology Raceway is a 1.25-mile (2.01 km) permanent D-shaped oval in Madison, Illinois. The Bommarito Automotive Group 500 is the ninth round of the 2026 NTT IndyCar Series season, contested over 260 laps (325 miles) under the lights on Sunday, June 7, at 9 p.m. ET. Coming on the heels of the Indianapolis 500 and the Detroit Grand Prix, teams will switch to short-track wings for what promises to be an entertaining evening of racing.\n\nJosef Newgarden is a five-time winner at Gateway, including three victories in the current 260-lap format (2021, 2022, 2024), and enters as one of the contenders despite sitting eighth in the championship standings. Kyle Kirkwood is the defending race winner from 2025. Felix Rosenqvist arrives fresh off his Indianapolis 500 victory with significant momentum, while David Malukas enters as a favourite. Scott Dixon and Pato O'Ward have combined for multiple podiums at this venue. The last two IndyCar races at Gateway earned top billing as the best of the year each time, setting expectations high for another competitive night of racing.\n\nThe all-time IndyCar qualifying lap record at World Wide Technology Raceway belongs to Scott McLaughlin, who set a 24.5968-second lap (average) during qualifying for the 2023 Bommarito Automotive Group 500. The race fastest lap record belongs to Linus Lundqvist, who clocked a 25.6786 during the 2023 race.",
